# Court Documents

## What this stage is
This stage involves preparing and submitting formal documents required by the court if the child protection case goes to a hearing or legal proceedings.

## Common documents at this stage
- Affidavit (Form 35)
- Plan of Care
- Notice of Motion
- Motion Record
- Other court-related filings

## Purpose
These documents present your information, evidence, and requests to the court in an official format.

## Important note
Filling out these forms correctly and understanding their purpose is crucial as they are part of the formal legal process.
